Certainly! Below is a simple HTML game coded entirely in one file. This is a classic "Guess the Number" game, where the user has to guess a randomly generated number between 1 and 100. The UI and logic are all contained in the HTML―just copy and run!

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>Guess the Number Game</title>
  <style>
    body {
      font-family: sans-serif;
      background: #f8f8fc;
      max-width: 420px;
      margin: 2em auto;
      padding: 2em;
      border-radius: 10px;
      box-shadow: 0 2px 12px #bbb;
    }
    input[type="number"] {
      width: 70px;
      font-size: 1.2em;
    }
    button {
      font-size: 1em;
      margin-left: 0.5em;
    }
    .result {
      margin-top: 1em;
      font-weight: bold;
    }
    .attempts {
      font-size: 0.95em;
      color: #555;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>🎲 Guess the Number!</h1>
  <p>I'm thinking of a number between <b>1</b> and <b>100</b>.</p>
  <form id="gameForm">
    <input type="number" id="guessInput" min="1" max="100" required>
    <button type="submit">Guess</button>
    <button type="button" id="restartBtn">Restart</button>
  </form>
  <div class="result" id="result"></div>
  <div class="attempts" id="attempts"></div>
  <script>
    let number = Math.floor(Math.random() * 100) + 1;
    let attempts = 0;
    const form = document.getElementById('gameForm');
    const resultDiv = document.getElementById('result');
    const attemptsDiv = document.getElementById('attempts');
    const guessInput = document.getElementById('guessInput');
    const restartBtn = document.getElementById('restartBtn');

    function resetGame() {
      number = Math.floor(Math.random() * 100) + 1;
      attempts = 0;
      resultDiv.textContent = '';
      attemptsDiv.textContent = '';
      guessInput.value = '';
    }

    form.addEventListener('submit', function(e) {
      e.preventDefault();
      const guess = Number(guessInput.value);
      attempts++;
      if (guess === number) {
        resultDiv.textContent = `🎉 Correct! The number was ${number}. You guessed it in ${attempts} attempts.`;
        resultDiv.style.color = "green";
      } else if (guess < number) {
        resultDiv.textContent = '🔻 Too low! Try again.';
        resultDiv.style.color = "maroon";
      } else {
        resultDiv.textContent = '🔺 Too high! Try again.';
        resultDiv.style.color = "maroon";
      }
      attemptsDiv.textContent = `Attempts: ${attempts}`;
      guessInput.value = '';
      guessInput.focus();
    });

    restartBtn.addEventListener('click', resetGame);
  </script>
</body>
</html>
```

**How it works:**  
- Enter a guess (1–100) and click "Guess."
- You’ll get feedback (“Too low”, “Too high”) until you guess right.
- The number of attempts is tracked.
- Press "Restart" to start over anytime.

